How to build:
* Setup git and yasm 1.x.x environment. The macports is easy solution.
* NOTICE: This build requires Leopard+Xcode 3.1, or SnowLeopard+Xcode 3.2.
* clone git repository first

* get latest libx264, tag rev.number, create symlink
  $ cd repository-base-folder                      ### x264Encoder local repository
  $ mv x264 x264.org                               ### original x264 is symlink
  $ git clone git://git.videolan.org/x264.git x264
  $ cd x264
  $ NEWNAME="x264`git rev-list HEAD | sort | wc -l | awk '{ print $1; }'`"
  $ cd ..
  $ mv x264 ${NEWNAME}                             ### name would be x2641629 or so
  $ ln -s ${NEWNAME} x264                          ### recreate symlink
  $ cd x264                                        ### follow symlink
  $ cat ../x264.*.diff | patch -p1 -d.             ### apply patches
  $ cp -pr ../x264.org/x264.xcodeproj .            ### copy project file

* Get latest ffmpeg, tag rev.number, create symlink.
  $ cd repository-base-folder                      ### x264Encoder local repository
  $ mv libav libav.org                             ### original libav is symlink
  $ svn checkout svn://svn.mplayerhq.hu/ffmpeg/trunk
  $ cd trunk
  $ NEWNAME="libav`svn info | awk '/Revision:/ {print $2;}'`"
  $ cd ..
  $ mv trunk ${NEWNAME}                            ### name would be libav23501 or so
  $ ln -s ${NEWNAME} libav                         ### recreate symlink
  $ cd libav                                       ### follow symlink
  $ cat ../ffmpeg.*.diff | patch -p1 -d.           ### apply patches
  $ cp -pr ../libav.org/libav.xcodeproj .          ### copy project file

* build libx264.a using Xcode
  $ cd repository-base-folder                      ### x264Encoder local repository
  $ cd x264                                        ### follow symlink
  $ open x264.xcodeproj
  # build target : "Build Universal"
  :
  $ ls -l *.a
  -rw-r--r--   1 takashi  admin  1773608  6  4 10:45 libx264.a

* build libavcodec.a and others using Xcode
  $ cd repository-base-folder                      ### x264Encoder local repository
  $ cd libav                                       ### follow symlink
  $ open libav.xcodeproj
  # build target : "Build Universal"
  :
  $ ls -l *.a
  -rw-r--r--  1 takashi  admin  3608504  6  4 10:47 libavcodec.a
  -rw-r--r--  1 takashi  admin    66576  6  4 10:47 libavdevice.a
  -rw-r--r--  1 takashi  admin   835088  6  4 10:47 libavformat.a
  -rw-r--r--  1 takashi  admin   356432  6  4 10:47 libavutil.a
  -rw-r--r--  1 takashi  admin   946176  6  4 10:47 libswscale.a

* build UIbundle.bundle using Xcode.
  $ cd repository-base-folder                      ### x264Encoder local repository
  $ cd UIbundle
  $ open UIbundle.xcodeproj
  # build target : "UIbundle"

* build x264Encoder.component using Xcode.
  $ cd repository-base-folder                      ### x264Encoder local repository
  $ cd source
  $ open x264Encoder.xcodeproj
  # build target : "Build and Copy"

NOTE: This build target will copy x264Encoder.component into /Library/QuickTime/. Not /Users/XXX/Library/QuickTime/.
